<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-E95ECE1D-7AD0-4F00-872B-18F985F2418C" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-E95ECE1D-7AD0-4F00-872B-18F985F2418C" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title "> Explanation and use of the Demo print</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-60408402-60FB-4280-8E98-976257B6A8B8"><p class="- topic/p "> The output of the demo print is dependent on the hardware configuration and functionality that is available.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The purpose of this print is to demonstrate to the customer what the print looks like after installation instead of showing a PQT (Print Quality Test) without the RIP (Raster Image Processor) being installed.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The print should show no artifacts.
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-FCCCBBA1-3996-4617-83C0-E78C1A39AB95" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Demo Print</title><table id="GUID-0E8E425D-E2FB-417D-BE55-B2DEFD126324" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="30*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="60*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Image
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Information 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Image
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Demo print specialty gloss.
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-D616BAC6-A2A4-4736-B7D7-6445D47E31FC" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B25F37BF-7AE5-4171-92FE-5F8A59E425A6-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B25F37BF-7AE5-4171-92FE-5F8A59E425A6-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Demo print in specialty matte.
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-8B668EA2-DC50-4259-81DF-ED4C2B0CEEC4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-5772FCB6-5003-44EC-9157-6E43680440EB-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-5772FCB6-5003-44EC-9157-6E43680440EB-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Demo print FLXfinish+.
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-CBEAF1E9-1558-4154-8E2B-C8189D8F1F9F" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-A5053EB0-3B0A-44CD-BE85-157ACDA0DA8E-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-A5053EB0-3B0A-44CD-BE85-157ACDA0DA8E-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> Demo print White.
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-827930A9-C85A-481D-B704-8AB43348901B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-222AFA2F-5FBA-4884-9AD4-CA88725665C9-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-222AFA2F-5FBA-4884-9AD4-CA88725665C9-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table><p class="- topic/p "> The delay between prints 1, 2 and 3, and between prints 3 and 4, is caused by temperature adjustments.
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Between print 2 and print 3 about 1 minute due to temperature change from 24 to 21 degrees C.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Between print 3 and 4 about 5 minutes due to temperature change from 21 to 36 degrees C.
</p></li></ul><p class="- topic/p "> The spit bar in print 3 and print 4 at the right side is normal behavior to keep all nozzles in condition.
</p><note id="GUID-9EFD50AD-9E68-45EA-8CC0-3D660404FA53" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p "> When printing the Demo print, you must select a media.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> If you select:
</p></note><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Service tests media Vinyl/Film/Paper</b>:<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> 
</b>
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The default media settings will be used for each of the test prints and cannot be changed.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> All customer media</b>: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The media-related settings as defined in the RIP will be applied. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Using incorrect settings may result in PQ artifacts.
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Do not print on porous/open media, such as uncoated paper, as the gloss printed ink may not fully cure.
</p></li></ul></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-EF42FFF3-C6AF-4939-AE5C-9EB2061E0E1B.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Image Quality</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>